
======================================================================
INSTALL-004 Language package manager invoked in install hook [CRITICAL]
======================================================================

Category:
  Malicious Code  (detector: rules)

Description:
  An install scriptlet invokes a language package manager to
  fetch/install packages. Installing a package runs its arbitrary
  build/lifecycle scripts (preinstall, build.rs, setup.py, go
  generate, ...) at install time -- a remote code execution vector.
  The June 2026 Atomic Arch campaign used `npm install` this way
  (see ATOMIC-002); the same applies to pip, poetry, uv, pdm, cargo,
  go, gem, composer, conda, deno, and others.

Recommendation:
  Install hooks must never fetch or install packages. Declare real
  dependencies in depends/makedepends and handle sources in the
  source= array; report the package to the AUR maintainers.

CWE: CWE-494

======================================================================
